I can reproduce this by creating a new default alloy app:
index.js:
{code}
function doClick(e) {
    Ti.API.info("Hi there");
    alert($.label.text);
}

$.win.open();
{code}

index.xml:
{code}
<Alloy>
	<Window class="container" id="win">
		<Label id="label" onClick="doClick">Hello, World</Label>
	</Window>
</Alloy>
{code}

The log says:

-- Start application log -----------------------------------------------------
[INFO] :   Finished launching the application
[INFO] :   Waiting for app to connect to log relay
[INFO] :   ACS Login Results for environment `development`:
[INFO] [object Object]
-- End application log -------------------------------------------------------

The Ti.API.info("Hi there"); is not printed when I click the label
